  "texts": [
    "Let us define the normalized Gibbs distribution:",
    "where Z(q) = π ref (a ′ | q) exp 1 β r ϕ (a ′, q) da ′ is the partition function.",
    "Taking the logarithm of π *:",
    "Substituting log π ref (a | q) + 1 β r ϕ (a, q) = log π * (a | q) + log Z(q) into the objective:",
    "Since β > 0 and log Z(q) does not depend on π, maximizing J (π) is equivalent to minimizing the KL divergence D KL (π∥π *)."
  ],
